Decisions Made
- Standardized batch validation contracts on `candidate_set_id` plus `work_item_ids`.
- Made `validate record` the authoritative validation state transition path and documented `execute complete` as a reviewing-only action.
- Enforced BUILD_PLAN gating on `verify` and non-null `complexity` in the task completion hook.
- Restored stale-write protection for verb-mode state commits by requiring `based_on_revision`.

Problems Encountered
- `state-commit` verb mode accepted stale writes because it derived `expected_revision` from current state.
- VRM prompt output and schema had diverged between single-item and batch candidate models.
- Recovery and run-skill docs had drifted from the active-candidate-set model and conflicted during rebase.
- Rebase on top of latest `origin/main` produced conflicts in recovery and run-skill contracts.

Constraints Identified
- Runtime behavior is split between executable scripts/hooks and `SKILL.md`/prompt contracts; many fixes required contract alignment rather than new runtime code.
- All state writes must continue to flow through `state-commit`.
- Existing user changes in the worktree could not be discarded.

Open Questions
- Whether a future standalone `agent-atelier` CLI should replace or supplement the current skill-driven runtime surface.
- Whether higher-level end-to-end orchestration integration tests should be added beyond current contract and mutation coverage.

Context
- Implemented follow-up fixes from the orchestration v0.2 review against the two-tier state / batch candidate design notes.
- Rebased `feedback-analysis` onto `origin/main` before finalizing the contract alignment changes.
- Verified the resulting branch with `bash tests/all.sh`.

